# Revisions of large-scale formatting/style changes excluded from `git blame`.
#
# GitHub: auto-applies this file when present in repo root (verified
# docs.github.com 2026-05-12). Shows banner "Ignoring revisions in
# .git-blame-ignore-revs" on blame view. No viewer setup needed.
# Caveat: commit is only ignored if it INTRODUCED or MODIFIED lines —
# last-to-modify-line attribution still surfaces the commit.
#
# Local CLI: `git config blame.ignoreRevsFile .git-blame-ignore-revs`.
#
# Canonical pattern: biomejs/biome itself lists their own mass-format
# commits ("switch from tabs to spaces" etc.) in their .git-blame-ignore-revs.

